as awakened on one server, it was known what the consequences of waking the Sleeper are: mainly, that once all four dragon Warders have been killed at once (the trigger to awake the Sleeper), they never respawn again.<br><br>This effectively stops the appearance of certain items that only the Warders drop, and slows the gain of certain weapons which the Warders drop more of than other creatures within the zone.<br><br>Many consider this a bad thing, as guilds that had not yet had the opportunity to fight those Warders never will.  Only the players that do so first will, degenerating the game into a mere race.<br><br>Some guilds have become more malicious in their power, purposefully farming the Warders for their own gain, and then waking the Sleeper to prevent any others from doing the same.  It saddens me that such acts would be allowed, under the guise of simply 'playing the game.'<br><br>This creates a scenerio where one guild can become the most powerful on a server, and prevent any others from reaching their status.  Did you intend such a thing to occur?<br><br>Reasons some have awakened the Sleeper are mostly 'because it's there,' or 'to be first.'<br><br>In summary, the changes to Sleeper's Tomb after the Sleeper has been awakened do more harm to other players that any good one can imagine; in that it removes the freedom of opportunity to participate in certain encounters or gain certain items.  I have some suggestions though, that could be done to eliminate this harm:<br><br>Have the zone reset back to its original form on server resets.  So any may have the chance to kill the Warders or awake the Sleeper after a reset.  This falls short on a roleplay explanation though, and hinders the development of a dynamic world.<br><br>Another option would be to have all creatures remain in Sleeper's Tomb, with a variant on their names, and /says: such as Failed, Fallen, or Defeated Warders, who have let the Sleeper free, but are still around to be encountered by others.<br><br>Thank you for hearing out my concerns and suggestions.  I will prompt others who feel the same to send feedbacks so that the severity of these concerns is realized.<br><br>&lt;HR&gt;<br><br>Imbris <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukuldiinuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KuldiinUK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(11/18/01 9:34:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=608.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Concerns and Suggestions on the Scripted Changes to Slee</span><hr size=1> Give people a dynamic world, they bitch<br><br>Dont give them a dynamic world, they bitch.<br><br> <p><BR>Kuldiin Linguist<BR>60 Assassin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F25><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umecca11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mecca11</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(11/18/01 10:30:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=608.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Concerns and Suggestions on the Scripted Changes to Slee</span><hr size=1> /yawn<br><br><br>this seems to be the standard issue on all servers when the sleeper is released.<br><br>but email all ya want <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umyrrhimbris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>My